1. Types of Network Cables
a. Straight-Through Cable
Used to connect different types of devices, such as:

PC to Switch

Switch to Router

Wires are in the same order on both ends (usually T568A to T568A or T568B to T568B).

b. Crossover Cable
Used to connect similar devices, such as:

PC to PC

Switch to Switch

One end uses T568A, and the other end uses T568B.

c. Roll-Over Cable
Used to connect a PC to a router or switch console port for configuration.

Not used for normal data transmission.

